                            <comment id="13316721" author="honza889" created="Thu, 3 Nov 2016 08:36:11 -0400"  >&lt;p&gt;Require &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/wildfly-security/wildfly-elytron/pull/434&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/wildfly-security/wildfly-elytron/pull/434&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.jboss.org/browse/ELY-473&quot; title=&quot;True credential forwarding support&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;ELY-473&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;ELY-473&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; which is not merged yet.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13320251" author="honza889" created="Thu, 10 Nov 2016 07:44:41 -0500"  >&lt;p&gt;PR &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/wildfly-security/wildfly-elytron/pull/544&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/wildfly-security/wildfly-elytron/pull/544&lt;/a&gt; ensure pushing of delegating GSSCredential into SecurityIdentity.&lt;br/&gt;
What is not solved yet is its obtaining from SecurityIdentity in deployment:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;cite&gt;one idea could be the ability to obtain an AuthenticationContext that when in the container is backed by configuration in the subsystem, that in turn could reference a SecurityDomain.&lt;/cite&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;cite&gt;This then becomes the API that can be used to access the GSSCredential. Where we use a delegated GSSCredential we will need to tie that with the AuthenticationContext anyway so it may naturally become the API that can be used for that specific problem&lt;/cite&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
